",["$r","p",null,{"children":["One important principle in React is ",["$r","em",null,{"children":"local reasoning"}],": the ability to understand what a component or hook does by looking at its code in isolation. Hooks should be treated like “black boxes” when they are called. For example, a custom hook might have used its arguments as dependencies to memoize values inside it:"]}],"
